<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-9084] TotalOrderPartitioner fails on hadoop running on top of gpfs (or any parallel or distributed filesystem)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-9084</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running a job who uses TotalOrderPartitioner (like TeraSort or BulkImport of HBase) on hadoop running on top of gpfs (instead of hdfs) the program fails to find the file _partition.lst because is looking for it in the wrong directory. The confusion is between local fs meaning not hdfs and local meaning distributed fs. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
